# Google Apps Script web-app URL that receives waitlist signups and appends a
# row to your Google Sheet.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Open your waitlist Google Sheet → Extensions → Apps Script.
#   2. Paste the contents of waitlist-apps-script.gs and Save.
#   3. Deploy → New deployment → Web app:
#        - Execute as: Me
#        - Who has access: Anyone
#   4. Copy the Web app URL (ends in /exec) and paste it below.
#   5. Copy this file to ".env" and restart the dev server (npm run dev).
#
# In production, set the SAME variable in your host's env settings
# (e.g. Vercel/Netlify project → Environment Variables).
VITE_SHEET_ENDPOINT=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Influence Card (/influence) — real creator media-kit data
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Base URL of the Creasume backend (the Express API in ../Creasume/backend).
# Defaults to http://localhost:5000 when blank. In production set this to your
# deployed API origin (e.g. https://creasume.onrender.com).
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# NOTE: which creator the media kit shows now comes from the URL —
# /influence/<username> loads that creator. A bare /influence shows the demo.
# VITE_INFLUENCE_USERNAME is no longer used and can be removed.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Sign-In (the "Sign in with Google" button on /login and /signup)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OAuth 2.0 Web client ID from Google Cloud Console:
#   APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → OAuth client ID →
#   Application type: Web application.
#   • Authorized JavaScript origins: your frontend origins, e.g.
#       http://localhost:5173  and  https://your-site.vercel.app
#   • Copy the "Client ID" (ends in .apps.googleusercontent.com).
# This MUST be the SAME value as the backend's GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, or the ID
# token's `aud` won't match and verification fails. Leave blank to hide the
# Google button (the email/password + phone flows still work).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
